com.inqwell.any

Interface Vectored

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Any, Composite, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractArray, AbstractButtonGroup, AbstractProcess, AnyArray, AnyArrowButton, AnyBox, AnyButton, AnyButtonGroup, AnyByteArray, AnyCAction, AnyCard, AnyCButtonGroup, AnyCCheck, AnyCDockable, AnyCDropDown, AnyCheck, AnyClient.ClientUserProcess, AnyCMenu, AnyComboBox, AnyComponent, AnyCPanelPopup, AnyCRadio, AnyDateChooser, AnyDesktopPane, AnyDialog, AnyDocument, AnyDocView, AnyElement, AnyFileChooser, AnyFrame, AnyGrid, AnyInternalFrame, AnyLabel, AnyLabelFor, AnyLayoutContainer, AnyList, AnyMenu, AnyMenuBar, AnyMultipleCDockable, AnyOrderedMap, AnyPopupMenu, AnyProgressBar, AnyQueue, AnyRadio, AnySelection, AnySimpleComponent, AnySingleCDockable, AnySlider, AnySortView, AnySpinner, AnySplit, AnyTabbedPane, AnyTable, AnyText, AnyToggleButton, AnyToolBar, AnyTree, AnyView, AnyWindow, BasicProcess, BasicProcess.RootMap, ClientMonitor, Clipboard, DeadlockScanner, InstanceHierarchyMap, IoProcess, NodeSpecification, ProxyProcess, ServerListener, ServerMonitor, UserProcess, VectoredSet

    public interface Vectored
extends Composite
    Defines the characteristics of vectoring for an Any composite. If the implementation of a Composite interface or derived can support vectored access then it can implement this interface.

      • addByVector

        void addByVector(Any value)
        Places the given value at the end of the collection. If the implementation is a map then a suitable key will be invented for the value, for example its identity.

      • addByVector

        void addByVector(int at,
                 Any value)
        Places the given value at the specified location in the collection. If the location is not in the range 0 to entries() then an exception is generated unless the collection can be sparse. If setSparse(true) has previously been called then place-holders are inserted as required.

        If the implementation is a map then a suitable key will be invented for the value, for example its identity.
